message.content: To achieve a modern look with a leather sofa, choose a tan or light gray color to match your current decor. Add colorful pillows in teal or brown for a pop of color and maintain a minimalist style with sleek, clean lines. This will create a cohesive and stylish space!

design_analysis.current_style: The room has a neutral and minimalist design with a white sectional sofa, light curtains, and a beige textured rug. The color palette is soft and calming.
design_analysis.suggested_sofa: A modern leather sofa in a tan or light gray color would complement the existing neutral tones. Consider a sleek design with clean lines and metal or wooden legs to maintain the contemporary feel.
design_analysis.accessories: Incorporate colorful throw pillows in teal or brown to add contrast and interest. A soft throw blanket can also add texture.
design_analysis.additional_decor: Include a few decorative elements like a modern floor lamp or an artistic wall piece to enhance the design.

analysis.user_friendly_response: To achieve a modern look with a leather sofa, choose a tan or light gray color to match your current decor. Add colorful pillows in teal or brown for a pop of color and maintain a minimalist style with sleek, clean lines. This will create a cohesive and stylish space!
